\begin_body

\begin_layout Standard

\emph on
Look and feel
\emph default
 plays an vital role in the commercial success of every application; therefore
 at design time close attention should be payed in planning its structure.
 
\emph on
User-friendliness
\emph default
 is an important feature that any UI should fulfill, it can be decomposed
 in many characteristics: 
\emph on
navigability
\emph default
 (links between pages are to be designed to make the transition between
 pages easy, depth of levels of navigation and number of links shouldn't
 be too many), 
\emph on
accessibility
\emph default
 (the information should be available for any browser), 
\emph on
usability 
\emph default
(user should be able to master the application without technical expertise)
 and 
\emph on
readability
\emph default
 (information should be presented in an adequate format and in balanced
 amount).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
For 
\emph on
myTaxiService
\emph default
 the minimal requirements are those that were stated in the RASD, in particular:
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
TS is meant for user without any particular knowledge or experience in the
 field of IT so the application must be intuitive and easy to master (usability
 and readability).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Every functionality shall be reached surfing no more than 4 pages (navigability).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This section will be structured in two parts: in the first one new mockups
 will be provided and in the second UX diagrams will be shown.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
User interface mockups
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Starting from the mockups provided in the RASD we will extend the functionalists
 covered providing new representations, however we do not intend to show
 all possible pages.
 As usual, they are not constraining the implementation.
\end_layout

